  "datePublished": "2025-12-26",
  "description": "The fundamental group is an algebraic snapshot of the \u0026ldquo;holes\u0026rdquo; in a topological space. It answers a basic geometric question: if you walk in a loop, starting and ending at the same point, can you continuously shrink that loop down to a single point, or does the shape of the space force the loop to wrap around something? Loops that can be shrunk to a point are trivial. Loops that cannot are evidence of a hole. The fundamental group collects and organizes all the essentially different loops through a point.\n",
  "name": "Fundamental Group",
